<section xml:id="sec-definition-polynomials" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Definition</title>

  <p> Let <m>R</m> be a ring with unity. We give definition of a polynomial in one inderminate with coefficients in a ring <m>R</m>. </p>
  <definition xml:id="def-polynomial">
    <title>Definition of a polynomial</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        A polynomial in one indeterminate with coefficients in a ring <m>R</m> is defined as a map <m>P\colon\mathbb{Z}_{\geq 0}\to R</m> such that the image of <m>n\in\Z_{\geq 0}</m> under <m>P</m> is denoted by <m>P_n</m> and the set <m>{\mathrm supp}\,P=\{n\in\mathbb{Z}_{\geq 0}:P_n\neq 0\}</m> is finite.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
  <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Given <m>r\in R</m> we define <m>r\colon\Z_{\geq 0}\to R</m> such that <m>0\mapsto r</m> and <m>n\mapsto 0</m> for all <m>n\in\N</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </example>

    <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        We define <m>X\colon\Z_{\geq 0}\to R</m> such that <m>1\mapsto 1</m> and <m>n\mapsto 0</m> for all <m>n\neq 1</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </example>


</section>